name: openapi-pydantic
documentation_summary: The GitHub repository "mike-oakley/openapi-pydantic" is a public project that provides an implementation of the OpenAPI schema using Pydantic. It supports both Pydantic versions 1.8+ and 2.x, following the OpenAPI specification for class naming. This library, a fork of the no longer maintained OpenAPI Schema Pydantic version 1.2.4, allows for the construction of OpenAPI objects using Pydantic models or dictionaries, supporting various OpenAPI versions and offering compatibility with major Pydantic versions. It includes features for using Pydantic classes as schema objects and handling non-Pydantic schema types. The project is licensed under the MIT License and has garnered 33 stars and 4 forks on GitHub.
